<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-615-321  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 615 321.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  Dec 1990 v3 n12 p180(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sharyn Venit on desktop publishing. (Pro Tips) (tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Venit, Sharyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TutorialDesktop publishingGraphics SoftwareBar GraphsSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Sharyn Venit on Desktop PublishingandM;Here's how to produce a perfectly scaled bar chart and add some touches thatspreadsheets and even specialized graphing can't create.andM;Many drawing programs, such as Adobe Illustrator and Corel Draw, let youscale rectangles numerically, which is easier than using your eyes and amouse.andM;To start, determine the width of each bar.andP;  If the text width on the page is7 inches and your chart has six bars, you might make each bar 1 inch wide andreserve an inch for axis labels and space between bars.andM;Using the Rectange tool, draw a rectangle the wdith of one bar and the heightof 1 inch, 10 picas, or 100 points, depending on the unit of measure you'reworking in.andP;  This height will represent 1, 10, 100 or 1,000 units in thechart, or whatever power of 10 is closest to the median value of your bars.andO;If the values of your bars range from 550 to 1,500, the median would be about1,000.andM;Make as many copies of this median unit as you need for bars and arrange themalong a horizontal line.andP;  Scale each bar vertically by entering numericvalues in a dialog box.andP;  In Corel Draw, select a bar and, from the Transformmenu, choose the Stretch and Mirror dialog box, which lets you stretch thebars vertically by a percentage as shown in the table below.andP;  In AdobeIllustrator, press Alt and click the scale tool pointer on the base of a barto get the Scale dialog box.andP;  Then enter non-uniform scaling in percentages.andM;Derive the percentage values by moving the decimal in the value you wish eachbar to represent.andP;  The following table shows percentages used in creating abar chart with values that range from 550 to 1,500.andM;After scaling each bar, select all bars and use the same tool or command tostretch the chart to fit the space while maintaining proportions.andP;  Addfinishing touches such as axes, titles and artwork.andM;Sharyn Venit, a co-owner of TechArt in San Francisco, has co-written ninebooks on electronic publishing.andO;</TEXT></DOC>